{
  "stem": "22447.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was told to report in Hounslow Barracks, where they were all fusiliers because that was, in the First World War, there was a Jewish battalion, they were all fusiliers so they knew all the holidays and everything, the Jewish holidays.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was able to go home nearly every day from Whitechapel Station to Hounslow on the Underground.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I was able to go back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I was quite fortunate in that respect.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1940.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, there was a Jewish battalion in the First World War, and they were all fusiliers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And if you go to the Royal Fusiliers Museum in the Tower of London, they've got a life-sized cardboard cut out of David Ben-Gurion, who was a corporal in 1915, and he didn't like English politics so he left.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was very strange.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you're coming out of the kosher home, and a-- a kosher house, and then you're suddenly thrown into a thing like that, you go in the morning for breakfast, they're having sausages or kidneys, or a mug of tea and bread and butter, and the smell was horrific.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You couldn't eat it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I was fortunate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When you get there, after a few days, you go to see a welfare officer, and he calls all the new recruits together, like, individually, says, have you any problems?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There wasn't many that were married, a very few were married, or have you got a mortgage to pay or any problems?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said-- I said, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said, nothing else?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I said, well, there's just one thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'm of Jewish faith, and I don't eat the meat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he said, well, if there'd be a quorum of 10, that they order special meals but for one, they can't order the whole military organization for it.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
